dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_3658  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 18/5/2018 Pim\nrule: NAS_CPLX_1\nrationale: Ribosomes are present in the axonal compartment (Fig.1, RL22 used as marker protein using the RiboTag mouse line; electron and fluorescence microscopy) and protein translation is shown to occur in this compartment (PMID:27321671). RS27 is a generally accepted constituent of the ribosome. No functions of RS27 are known independent from the ribosomal complex. Inference to term \"ribosome (GO:0005840)\" part_of \"presynapse (GO:0098793)\" is trivial.\nC_ref CC: SynGO ID #1681 (\"presynaptic ribosome\")\nP_inf CC: SynGO ID #3656\nComplex membership: RS27 protein is a fixed member of the 40S ribosomal subunit complex.\n- Shown in crystal structure (PMID:28138070, Fig.1, name:es27)\n- GO annotations to \"structural constituent of ribosome (GO:0003735)\" (ISO and IEA). Experimental description: Title: \"Comparative Study of Human and Mouse Postsynaptic Proteomes Finds High Compositional Conservation and Abundance Differences for Key Synaptic Proteins\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3658" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

